To create a CSS variable, you just need to give a name with two hypens in front of it and
assign it a value like this:

--penguin-skin: gray;

once you declare the variable you will apply the variable to the other attributes using the
syntaxis:

var(--penguin-skin)

you will use a fallback variable like this:
var(--penguin skin, black) the color black will be applied if some issue occurs with the first value
assigned to the variable.

